            "question": "A fair coin is tossed 5 times. What is the probability of getting exactly 3 heads?",
            "difficulty": "hard",
            "hasDiagram": false,
            "options": {
                "A": "10.0/2^5",
                "B": "5/2^5",
                "C": "1/2^5",
                "D": "20/2^5"
            },
            "answer": "A",
            "hint": "Use Binomial distribution: nCr * (1/2)^r * (1/2)^(n-r)",
            "solution": "P(X=3) = 5C3 * (1/2)^n = 10.0/2^5.",
